# 15. 3Sum

## Problem Statement

Given an integer array `nums`, return all unique triplets:

```java id="p6k2vx"
[nums[i], nums[j], nums[k]]
```

such that:

```java id="d9m4sq"
i != j
i != k
j != k
```

and:

```java id="x1z7tw"
nums[i] + nums[j] + nums[k] == 0
```

The solution should not contain duplicate triplets.

---

# Example

## Input

```java id="m8r2np"
nums = [-1,0,1,2,-1,-4]
```

## Output

```java id="g5t9lc"
[[-1,-1,2],[-1,0,1]]
```

---

# Brute Force Approach

Use 3 loops:

```java id="f4v8dj"
for i
   for j
      for k
```

Check every triplet.

### Time Complexity

```java id="n2x6qm"
O(n³)
```

This is too slow.

---

# Optimal Approach (Sorting + Two Pointers)

## Main Idea

1. Sort the array
2. Fix one element
3. Use two pointers to find remaining two numbers

---

# Why Sorting?

After sorting:

```java id="z7c1ph"
[-4,-1,-1,0,1,2]
```

we can:

* move left pointer to increase sum
* move right pointer to decrease sum

This reduces complexity to:

```java id="t5b9vk"
O(n²)
```

---

# Algorithm

For every index `i`:

* Fix `nums[i]`
* Use:

```java id="r1m6qy"
left = i + 1
right = n - 1
```

* Calculate:

```java id="k3x8pd"
sum = nums[i] + nums[left] + nums[right]
```

### Cases

### 1. sum == 0

Triplet found.

Store it and move both pointers.

---

### 2. sum < 0

Need bigger value.

Move:

```java id="u7w2lf"
left++
```

---

### 3. sum > 0

Need smaller value.

Move:

```java id="b4n9xt"
right--
```

---

# Important Duplicate Handling

## Duplicate i

```java id="e2v5rc"
if(i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i - 1])
```

Skip duplicate first elements.

---

## Duplicate left

```java id="h6k1zs"
while(left < right &&
      nums[left] == nums[left - 1])
```

Skip duplicate left values.

---

## Duplicate right

```java id="q9j4wb"
while(left < right &&
      nums[right] == nums[right + 1])
```

Skip duplicate right values.

---

# Correct Java Code

```java id="y5f8na"
class Solution {

    public List<List<Integer>> threeSum(int[] nums) {

        List<List<Integer>> ans = new ArrayList<>();

        int n = nums.length;

        Arrays.sort(nums);

        for (int i = 0; i < n - 2; i++) {

            // Skip duplicate first elements
            if (i > 0 && nums[i] == nums[i - 1]) {
                continue;
            }

            int left = i + 1;
            int right = n - 1;

            while (left < right) {

                int sum =
                    nums[i] + nums[left] + nums[right];

                // Triplet found
                if (sum == 0) {

                    ans.add(Arrays.asList(
                        nums[i],
                        nums[left],
                        nums[right]
                    ));

                    left++;
                    right--;

                    // Skip duplicate left values
                    while (left < right &&
                           nums[left] == nums[left - 1]) {
                        left++;
                    }

                    // Skip duplicate right values
                    while (left < right &&
                           nums[right] == nums[right + 1]) {
                        right--;
                    }
                }

                // Need bigger sum
                else if (sum < 0) {
                    left++;
                }

                // Need smaller sum
                else {
                    right--;
                }
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
```

